   [white_space.gif]
   Ordering a Special Interest or Personalized Environmental License
   Plate.
    1. Choose the plate you want:

       Personalized Environmental or Special Interest Plate.
       The following Special Interest plates are currently available.
       Plates in the left column are available in Environmental License plate
       configurations. Plates in the right column receive standard sequential
       numbering.

       Personalized Plates   Sequential Only

       Arts
       Coastal Protection
       Collegiate^**
       ELP
       Firefighters
       Kids
       Lake Tahoe Conservancy
       Olympic Training
       Yosemite
       Veterans

                             Pearl Harbor Survivor^*
                             Purple Heart Recipient^*
                             Congressional Medal of Honor^*
                             Legion of Valor^*
                             Prisoner of War^*
                             Horseless Carriage
                             Antique Motorcycle
                             Historical Vehicle
                             Press Photographer^*
                             Amatuer Radio License^*
       ^* These plates require either certification or documentation.
       ^** Currently only UCLA is available
    2. Choose either a sequential or environmental configuration license
       plate. If you choose a sequential plate skip to step 4.
    3. Use the online search to determine if your personalized plate is
       available.
    4. View information and download the Adobe PDF ^* application form, or
       visit your local DMV office to reserve your plate configuration.

       ^* Adobe Portable Document Format (PDF) files require Adobe's free
       Acrobat Reader
